<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>美国之音学习英语</title><description>VOA学习英语全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> http://voanews.com <item><title><![CDATA[Landmines Causing More Casualties in Ukraine and Myanmar]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/landmines-causing-more-casualties-in-ukraine-and-myanmar/7358229.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 11 月 17 日星期五 21:55:18 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/50b8bd76- ab44-4b0b-9985-7f12f5a94973_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;文件 - 一个写着“地雷”的标志被放置在路边2023 年 2 月 19 日，乌克兰卡米扬卡村。在乌克兰东北部这座饱受战争创伤的城市，居民仔细检查每一步是否有地雷。（Vadim Ghirda/美联社照片）&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;一份国际报告显示，去年乌克兰和缅甸地雷使用的增加导致这些国家的&lt;strong>;伤亡&lt;/strong>;急剧上升。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;国际禁止地雷运动创建了这份名为&lt;em >;地雷监测 2023&lt;/em>;。这家总部位于瑞士的集团提供世界地雷使用的研究和监测服务。该组织是由人权观察组织支持的非政府组织联盟。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;报告中研究的装置被称为杀伤人员地雷。这意味着这些地雷是针对人类而不是坦克或其他军事装备而建造的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;报告指出，俄罗斯“自全面入侵乌克兰以来，在乌克兰&lt;strong>;广泛&lt;/strong>;使用了杀伤人员地雷”。 2022 年 2 月该国。”该文件指出，俄罗斯并未加入禁止使用杀伤人员地雷的国际条约。杀伤人员地雷禁令协议于1997年完成，美国不是该协议的缔约国。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;报告还发现证据表明，作为禁雷条约一部分的乌克兰曾使用过反人员地雷。人员在伊济乌姆和哈尔科夫市及其周边地区布雷。据称，这些地雷是俄罗斯军队在该地区与乌克兰军队作战时发现的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;禁止地雷运动记录了 2022 年全球有 4,710 人受伤和死亡。这比前一年的 5,544 人伤亡有所下降。但在乌克兰，地雷造成的平民伤亡人数从 2021 年的 60 人增加到 2022 年的约 600 人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;马克·希兹奈 (Mark Hiznay) 供职于人权观察组织，并帮助撰写了这份新报告。他对俄罗斯在乌克兰军事行动中使用地雷表示担忧。希兹内表示，自禁雷条约获得批准以来，非该条约成员国俄罗斯首次对条约成员国乌克兰使用此类武器。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;希兹内表示，俄罗斯开始使用此类武器2014年，为支持乌克兰东部有争议的顿巴斯地区的亲俄分离主义势力而埋设地雷。 “俄罗斯在阿富汗和车臣等地广泛使用了地雷，”他说。 Hiznay 表示，他相信俄罗斯多年来向 35 或 38 个不同国家提供了地雷。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乌克兰表示将调查人权观察报告中的指控。该报告提供了乌克兰军队在与俄罗斯的战争中部署禁用杀伤人员地雷的“多起案件”的详细信息。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该报告称，85% 的伤亡是由地雷和“爆炸残留物”造成的去年的“战争”是平民。大约一半的伤亡人员是儿童。叙利亚 2022 年的伤亡人数最多，为 834 人。其次是乌克兰，有 608 人伤亡，其次是也门和缅甸，2022 年两国的伤亡人数均超过 500 人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在缅甸，Hiznay称政府自 1999 年以来一直在使用杀伤人员地雷。但近年来情况发生了变化。 “它只是更大了，”希兹奈说。 “政府军更多地使用地雷，各种非国家武装团体也更多地使用地雷。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;目前，已有 164 个国家签署了禁雷条约，禁止使用、储存、生产和开采地雷。杀伤人员地雷的运输。报告称，自条约生效以来，该条约的 30 个成员国已清除其领土上的所有雷区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;我是布莱恩·林恩。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;美国之音的丽莎·施莱因报道了这个故事。布莱恩·林恩 (Bryan Lynn) 改编了美国之音学习英语的报告。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;______________________________________________&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;伤亡 &lt;/strong>;–n.在事故或战争中受伤或死亡的人&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;监视&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;- v. &lt;/em>;仔细观察某事并记录结果&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;&lt;strong>;广泛&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;——形容词&lt;/em>;。覆盖或影响大面积&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;残余&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n. &lt;/em>;某物的一部分在其余部分消失后仍继续存在&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 18 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Is a Chinese Movie Keeping Away Visitors to Thailand?]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/is-a-chinese-movie-keeping-away-visitors-to-thailand-/7354820.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 11 月 17 日星期五 21:55:51 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- 0a00-0242-36e9-08dbe4588237_cx0_cy5_cw0_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;文件 - 中国游客抵达泰国北部清迈省的清迈国际机场， 2023 年 1 月 23 日。（美联社照片/Wichai Thaprieo）&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;一部展示东南亚&lt;strong>;诈骗&lt;/strong>;的中国电影可能会吓跑中国游客前往泰国，研究人员和数据表明。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;电影&lt;em>;No More Bets&lt;/em>;于八月上映。这是关于几名中国公民被骗去一个不知名的东南亚国家出差的故事。一旦到达那里，游客就被迫进行非法在线投资、&lt;strong>;赌博&lt;/strong>;和称为加密货币的数字货币。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这部电影是根据现实生活中的一个问题改编的，该问题在最近几年。电影上映的同一个月，联合国人权事务高级专员发布了一份关于犯罪集团的报告。据称，犯罪团伙迫使东南亚数十万人从事非法活动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在中国，《No More Bets》在发行第一个月就赚了超过 5 亿美元。它连续三周成为八月份的热门电影。它在今年的电影中票房第三高。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在电影中的某个时刻，&lt;strong>;被绑架的&lt;/strong>;中国旅行者乘坐一辆小型车辆行驶，该车辆在一辆小型车辆下行驶。 “素坤逸路”的路标。这是泰国首都曼谷的著名地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;专家表示，这部电影应该不会对中国赴泰旅游产生持久影响。但它引起了人们的担忧，担心它可能会吓到游客前往曼谷。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;泰国并不是这部电影的成功引起担忧的唯一国家。柬埔寨已禁止该片在该国上映，因为该片使用高棉语。在缅甸，该国军政府表示这部电影损害了国家形象。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Vincent Zhuang 曾为《罗博报告》工作，这是一份关于美好生活（包括旅行）的出版物。他仍然认为泰国是中国游客的好去处。但他承认坏消息很容易让一些可能的游客望而却步。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我从来不认为这会是一个大问题。今年我自己去了泰国。我们知道东南亚有很多有趣的地方，适合中国市场。”庄通过电子邮件对美国之音表示。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;《No More Bets》基于真实事件，这一事实对于&lt;strong>;观众&lt;/strong>;来说意义重大好吧，庄说。有证据表明，这部电影可能已经对前往泰国的中国游客产生了一些影响，因为入境人数低于预期。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府数据显示，今年截至 8 月份，前往泰国的中国大陆游客已超过 220 万人次找到了。但泰国旅游局预计，到 2023 年底，中国游客将达到 500 万。到下个月底，这个数字似乎不太可能达到。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;不过，还必须考虑其他原因。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;中国经济正在放缓。飞往泰国的&lt;strong>;航班&lt;/strong>;仍然没有达到大流行前的水平。除此之外，9月在曼谷发生的枪击事件造成三人死亡，其中包括一名中国公民。当地媒体报道称，枪击事件后，6万名中国游客取消了前往泰国的行程。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;我是格雷戈里·斯塔切尔。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;汤米·沃克报道了这一消息美国之音的故事。格雷戈里·斯塔切尔将其改编为美国之音英语学习频道。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;_________________________________________________________&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;骗局&lt;/strong>;–&lt;em>;n &lt;/em>;。通过欺骗他人来赚钱的不诚实方式&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;赌博&lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;。玩可以赢或输金钱或财产的游戏：赌钱或其他有价值的东西&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;绑架&lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;。强行将（某人）带离某个地方&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;旅游&lt;/strong>;-&lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;。前往某个地方休闲的活动&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;观看者&lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;。看电视的人&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;坐飞机&lt;/strong>;–&lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;。飞机旅行&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 18 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Doctor Heidegger’s Experiment by Nathaniel Hawthorne]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/nathaniel-hawthorne-doctor-heideggers-experiment/4307319.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 11 月 17 日星期五 21:59:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/09bb0000- 0a00-0242-6865-08da97fda8b8_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:100%&quot; 控件>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small>;&lt;/div >;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/09bb0000-0a00-0242-6865-08da97fda8b8_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;D&quot; style=&quot;width:100%&quot; 控件>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;D&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews. com/09bb0000-0a00-0242-6865-08da97fda8b8_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:100%&quot; 控件>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small >;&lt;/div>;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/09bb0000-0a00-0242-6865-08da97fda8b8_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;width: 100%”控制>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;0&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;audio src=&quot;https://av.voanews.com/clips/ VLE/2016/05/04/ec2de3fe-e1b9-46f3-af6d-cc7cf7bb3e9d_original.mp3&quot;controls>;&lt;/audio>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;纳撒尼尔·霍桑的海德格尔博士的实验&lt;/small >;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;&lt;br />; &lt;em>;我们展示纳撒尼尔·霍桑的短篇小说《海德格尔博士的实验》。它已针对英语学习者进行了改编。这是芭芭拉·克莱因的故事。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;那个非常不寻常的人，老海德格尔医生，曾经邀请四个朋友到他的办公室来见他。里面有三位白胡子先生，梅德伯恩先生、基利格鲁上校和加斯科因先生。还有，有一位瘦弱的老太太，她的丈夫去世了，所以她被称为威彻利寡妇。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们都是生活不幸的悲伤老生物。年轻时，梅德伯恩先生在一次计划不周的商业交易中损失了所有的钱。基利格鲁上校把他最好的年华和健康浪费在享受女人和饮酒的乐趣上。加斯科因先生是一位身败名裂的政治家，有着邪恶的过去。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;至于威彻利寡妇，传统告诉我们，她曾经是一位大美人。但有关她过去的令人震惊的故事导致镇上的人们拒绝她。因此，她非常孤独地生活。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;值得一提的是，这三个男人都是威彻利寡妇的早期恋人。他们曾经一度为了她而自相残杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我亲爱的老朋友们，”海德格尔医生说，“我希望你们能帮助我完成一个小实验。”他示意他们坐下。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;海德格尔医生的办公室是一个非常奇怪的地方。黑暗的房间里堆满了书籍、蜘蛛网和灰尘。据说两个书架之间挂着一面旧镜子，可以显示出医生所有死去病人的鬼魂。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另一面墙上挂着一幅海德格尔医生很久以前就要结婚的年轻女子的画。但她在婚礼前一天晚上喝了医生开的一种药后去世了。房间里最神秘的东西是一本用黑色皮革覆盖的大书。据说这是一本魔法书。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在我们故事的那个夏日午后，房间中央立着一张黑色的桌子。上面有一个漂亮的雕花玻璃&lt;strong>;花瓶&lt;/strong>;。桌子上还有四个玻璃杯。&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/34053309-27A2-47E4-991F-1F725ED7B3A9_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Vase&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;Vase&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;海德格尔博士因其不寻常的实验而闻名。但他的四位客人并没有想到会有什么非常有趣的事情。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;医生拿起​​了他的黑皮魔法书。他从书页中取出一朵干枯的老玫瑰。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这朵玫瑰，”医生说，“是西尔维娅·沃德 (Sylvia Ward) 于五十五年前送给我的，她的画就挂在这面墙上。我是在我们的婚礼上佩戴它。你认为这朵古老的玫瑰有可能再次绽放吗？”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“胡说！”威彻利寡妇摇摇头说道。 “你不妨问问老妇人的皱纹脸是否还能再次绽放。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“看！”海德格尔博士回答道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他伸手拿起花瓶，把干玫瑰扔进里面的水里。很快，变化开始出现。被压碎、干涸的花瓣动了动，慢慢地由棕色变成了红色。还有一朵半个世纪的玫瑰，看起来就像西尔维娅·沃德第一次送给她的爱人时一样新鲜。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是一个非常漂亮的技巧，”医生的朋友们说。 “秘密是什么？”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你听说过&lt;strong>;不老泉&lt;/strong>;吗？”海德格尔医生问道。 “几个世纪前，西班牙探险家庞塞·德莱昂就曾去寻找它。但他没有找对地方。如果我没获悉的话，著名的不老泉就在佛罗里达州南部。我的一个朋友给我送来了水你在花瓶里看到的。&quot;&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/B3D62337-CFA5-4A64-BCA7-2F061331C85D_w900.jpg&quot; alt =&quot;青春之泉，佛罗里达州圣约翰斯县圣奥古斯丁&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;青春之泉，佛罗里达州圣约翰斯县圣奥古斯丁&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;医生给四个杯子装满了不老泉的水。液体产生小气泡，上升到银色的表面。老客人们同意喝这水，尽管他们不相信它的力量。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“在喝之前，我的朋友们，”医生说，“在喝之前，你应该制定一些一般规则作为指导。你第二次经历了青春的危险。你有一生的经验来指导你。想想看，如果你的经验智慧不能充当指导和老师，那将是多么遗憾。”&lt;/p>; &lt;医生的四个朋友笑着回答他。他们会重复年轻时的错误的想法非常有趣。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“那就喝吧，”医生说。 “我很高兴我的实验对象选得这么好。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们把酒杯举到唇边。如果这种液体真的有魔力，就不可能给四个更需要它的人。他们似乎从未体验过青春和快乐。他们看起来就像一直是在医生桌子上弯腰的虚弱、不快乐的生物。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们喝了水。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;客人们的情况几乎立即得到改善。他们的脸上洋溢着阳光般的快乐光芒。他们面面相觑，想象着某种魔力真的开始抚平他们脸上的皱纹。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“快！给我们更多的&lt;strong>;神奇&lt;/strong>;水！”他们哭了。 “我们年轻了，但我们还是太老了！”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“耐心点！”海德格尔博士以科学的冷静观看了这次实验。 “你们老了好久了，等半个小时就可以变年轻了！”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他又给他们斟满了酒。四位客人一口气喝了下去。当液体流过他们的喉咙时，他们的整个系统似乎都发生了变化。他们的眼睛变得清澈明亮。他们的头发从银色变成了更深的色调。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我亲爱的寡妇，你真可爱！”基利格鲁上校喊道，他看着岁月的痕迹从她脸上消失。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;寡妇跑向镜子。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;三个男人开始表现出这样的行为方式，证明了&lt;strong>;青春之泉的魔力&lt;/strong>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;加斯科因先生的注意力转向了政治话题。他谈到了&lt;strong>;民族主义&lt;/strong>;和人民的权利。他还轻声地对自己诉说着秘密。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;基利格鲁上校一直在大声喊着快乐的饮酒歌曲，同时他的眼睛转向威彻利寡妇的曲线身材。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;梅德伯恩先生增加美元和美分来支付拟议项目的费用。它将通过将一群鲸鱼与极地冰山连接起来，为东印度群岛提供冰。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;至于威彻利寡妇，她站在镜子前向自己的形象打招呼，就像她最爱的朋友一样&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我亲爱的老医生，”她喊道，“请再给我一杯！”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;医生已经重新给杯子倒满了。现在已接近日落，房间比以前更暗。但花瓶内却发出月光般的光芒。医生坐在椅子上看着。当四位客人喝下第三杯水时，他们被医生那张神秘的脸上的表情弄得沉默了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;下一刻，激动人心的年轻生命在他们的血液中涌动。他们现在正处于青春快乐的顶峰。无尽的忧虑、悲伤和年老的疾病，只记得他们从一场噩梦中醒来。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们还年轻！”他们哭了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;客人是一群快乐的年轻人，精力充沛，几乎疯狂。他们嘲笑自己穿的老式衣服。他们高兴地喊着，在房间里跳来跳去。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;寡妇威彻利——如果这样的年轻女士可以被称为寡妇的话——跑到医生的椅子上，请他跳舞。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;”请原谅。”医生平静地回答。 “我跳舞的日子早就结束了。但是这三个年轻人会很高兴有这么可爱的舞伴。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;男人们开始激烈地争论谁要和她跳舞。他们聚集在寡妇周围，每个人都抓住她。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，由于房间的黑暗，据说高高的镜子通过一种奇怪的伎俩反射出了三个灰色老人的身影，他们在争夺权力。一个面色苍白的老妇人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当三个人为争夺那个女人的青睐而战斗时，他们猛烈地掐住了对方的喉咙。在他们的斗争中，他们掀翻了桌子。花瓶碎成一千块。青春之水在地板上流淌成明亮的溪流。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;客人们静静地站着。一种奇怪的寒冷正在慢慢地笼罩着他们。他们看着手捧着他心爱的玫瑰花的海德格尔医生。花儿又凋谢了，干枯了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;宾客们面面相觑，面色又变了。 “我们这么快就又老了吗？”他们哭了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;事实上他们哭了。青春之水的力量只是&lt;strong>;暂时的&lt;/strong>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“是的，朋友们，你又老了，”医生说。 “而青春之水就浪费在地上了，但即使流到了我家门口的河里，我也不会喝。这就是你给我的教训！”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但是医生的四个朋友没有吸取这样的教训。就在那一刻，他们决定前往佛罗里达州，早中晚都喝青春泉的水。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;现在轮到你使用这个故事中的文字了。你认为人们应该寻找青春之泉吗？你见过年长的人却试图表现得比实际年龄更年轻吗？请在评论部分给我们写信。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;__________________________________________________&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;对于教师&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;本课程计划基于CALLA 方法，教授预测策略，帮助学生理解故事。&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;测验&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;尝试此听力测验来检查您的理解情况。​ &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;​__________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;花瓶&lt;/strong>; - &lt;em>; n.&lt;/em>;用于盛放鲜花或装饰的容器&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;青春之泉&lt;/strong>; - &lt;em>;n。 &lt;/em>;1.在故事和传说中：带有神奇水的喷泉&lt;em>;或&lt;/em>;&lt;br />;年轻人通常拥有的能量或健康来源&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;奇妙&lt;/strong >; - &lt;em>;形容词。&lt;/em>;引起奇迹或惊奇 &lt;strong>;：&lt;/strong>;非常美丽或令人印象深刻&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;神奇&lt;/strong>; - &lt;em>;形容词。&lt;/ em>; 有能力让不可能的事情发生；拥有超自然力量&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;民族主义&lt;/strong>; - &lt;em>;n.&lt;/em>;人们对自己的国家忠诚并为之自豪的感觉，常常相信国家更好并且比其他国家更重要&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;临时&lt;/strong>; &lt;strong>;- &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;adj.持续有限的时间；不是永久的​&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 18 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Source or Resource?]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/source-or-resource-/7356369.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 11 月 17 日星期五 22:05:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- c0a8-0242-e4c4-08dbe6125020_r1_s.png&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;询问老师：来源还是资源？&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p >;你好！本周&lt;em>;向老师提问&lt;/em>;，我们将回答一个有关“源”和“资源”这两个词之间区别的问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;问题：&lt;/strong>;&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;朋友们大家好，&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;我是 Isac，是你们来自墨西哥的关注者之一。我有一个问题。“来源”和“资源”之间有什么区别？非常感谢。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;回答&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;谢谢你的问题，Isac。“source”和“resource”都有相似的词历史。一个是词根另一个。这就是它们看起来相似并且可能会混淆的原因。但这两个词完全不同！让我们分别考虑一下。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;来源&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; “来源”可以是名词，也可以是动词。&lt;strong>; &lt;/strong>;作为名词，“来源”是事物的起源或开始。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;例如，我们经常谈论来源河流的源头。这个源头是河流的发源地，就像另一个水体，例如湖泊。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;尼罗河有两个源头，青尼罗河和白尼罗河。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/00020000-0aff-0242-f635-08dabcea441e_w900.jpg &quot; alt=&quot;这张照片拍摄于 2022 年 10 月 7 日，40 岁的乔瓦利·基塔根达 (Jowali Kitagenda) 在乌干达南部金贾的尼罗河上撒网捕鱼。摄影：BADRU KATUMBA /法新社)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;这张照片拍摄于 2022 年 10 月 7 日，40 岁的乔瓦利·基塔根达 (Jowali Kitagenda) 在乌干达南部金贾的尼罗河上撒网捕鱼。照片由BADRU KATUMBA /法新社）&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;来源也可以是提供信息的人或诸如书籍或文章之类的东西。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot; >;&lt;em>;当你写一篇文章时，你应该写下你的来源。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;来源也可以是某物的组成部分。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin- left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;称为胭脂红的红色虫子是染料中使用的红色的来源。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url =gdb.voanews.com/01000000-0aff-0242-9dd7-08dbabfd998e_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Mayeli Garcia 在位于旧金山 Tepeyacac 的家族胭脂虫农场检查干燥、压碎的微小雌性昆虫，称为 Dactylopius coccus， 2023 年 8 月 24 日，墨西哥城东部。&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;Mayeli Garcia 在位于旧金山 Tepeyacac 的家族胭脂虫农场检查干燥、压碎的微小雌性昆虫，称为 Dactylopius coccus，墨西哥城东部，2023 年 8 月 24 日。&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;“来源”也可以是动词。它可以意味着为某事寻找材料，也可以意味着提供某事。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;厨师为这道菜采购&lt;strong>;配料&lt;/strong>;来自她自己的花园。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;许多珠宝公司采购实验室种植的钻石。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;让我们转到“资源”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;资源&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“资源”一词是一个名词。它有很多含义。 “资源”是指在需要时可以轻松找到并快速使用的东西。它可以是某种东西的供应、支持或援助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这种资源可以包括金钱、&lt;strong>;资产&lt;/strong>;或紧急情况下的人力。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style =&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;美国在冲突时期向其盟友提供军事资源。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;国际红十字与红新月会为遭受自然灾害的人们提供资源。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- 0aff-0242-8b43-08dbccf8b3c9_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;FILE - 2023 年 10 月 11 日，巴勒斯坦人聚集在贝鲁特红十字国际委员会办公室外守夜，支持加沙的巴勒斯坦人。（摄影： ANWAR AMRO / 法新社)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;文件 - 2023 年 10 月 11 日，巴勒斯坦人聚集在贝鲁特红十字国际委员会办公室外守夜，支持加沙的巴勒斯坦人。 （ANWAR AMRO / 法新社拍摄）&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;“资源”也可以是在地球环境中或其表面下自然发现的东西。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left :48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;自然资源包括金属、石油、水甚至阳光。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;最后，“资源”可以是可以帮助您获取信息的事物或人，或者是某个学科或行业的专家。&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;当她选择学习领域时，她的大学导师成为了她的宝贵资源。&lt;/em>;&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;Isac，请告诉我们这些解释和示例是否对您有帮助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;您对美式英语有疑问吗？请发送电子邮件至 &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:learningenglish@voanews.com&quot;>;learningenglish@voanews.com&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这就是&lt;em>;向老师提问&lt;/em>;。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;我是费思·皮尔洛。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;费思·皮尔洛为美国之音英语学习频道撰写了本课程。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;em>;______________________________________________&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;成分&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n。 &lt;/em>;进入化合物或者是任何组合或混合物的组成部分的东西&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;资产&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;- n。 &lt;/em>;拥有且有价值的东西&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 18 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Migrants Overwhelm Spain’s Canary Islands]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/migrants-overwhelm-spain-s-canary-islands/7356087.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 11 月 16 日星期四 21:55:32 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- 0a00-0242-b22a-08dbe6c499b8_cx2_cy12_cw95_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;几位志愿者在西班牙拉古纳的拉斯赖塞斯营地外为移民开设西班牙语课程， 2023 年 11 月 5 日。（路透社/博尔哈·苏亚雷斯）&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;15 岁的几内亚人穆萨·卡马拉 (Moussa Camara) 是今年抵达西班牙加那利群岛创纪录的 32,000 名移民之一。他们从非洲出发，经过一条极其危险的海路。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;穆萨的父母去世了。他上个月离开几内亚。这名少年与其他 240 名移民挤进一艘木船，前往加那利群岛。此次行程历时11天。他们没有足够的食物或淡水。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;旅行者说，有 20 人在旅途中死亡。他们所走的道路被认为是对移民来说最危险的道路之一。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卡马拉于 10 月 27 日抵达，又累又饿。他很快就面临另一个问题：警方将他登记为成年人。这意味着他不被允许进入有更好&lt;strong>;机会&lt;/strong>;的未成年人中心。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卡马拉和一位同样以成年人身份登记的朋友在特内里费岛山区的一个旧军事基地。在那里，大约 2,000 名移民正在等待转移到西班牙大陆或前往欧洲其他地方的许可。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;将他登记为成人意味着他在 18 岁之前不能获得额外的住房和教育支持，而必须独自养活自己。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;需要进行骨骼测试来证明他的年龄。但红十字会文件支持卡马拉的说法，即他已 15 岁，而不是警方所​​说的 18 岁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;加那利群岛总统费尔南多·克拉维霍 (Fernando Clavijo) 告诉路透社，登记问题表明政府已&lt;strong>;不知所措&lt;/strong>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们既没有资源，也没有冷静来应对即将到来的&lt;strong>;雪崩&lt;/strong>;，”他补充道。他指责警方处理错误，因为每天约有 100 名儿童进入加那利群岛。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说西班牙国家政府没有处理这个问题。他说，它只提出在 12 月之前将 347 名流动儿童转移到其他地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;“还会有更多的孩子来”&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;此外，人权组织大赦国际国际组织在最近的一份报告中表示，在加那利群岛成人中心采访的 29 名移民中，有 12 名实际上是未成年人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对于被错误识别为成年人的儿童，他们有责任找到一个援助组织来帮助他们。这些支持者可以要求对孩子进行骨骼测试以确认他们的年龄。然而，这个过程可能需要几个月的时间。&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-c0a8-0242-77a7-08dbe6c499c4_w900.jpg &quot; alt=&quot;2023 年 11 月 4 日，一群移民走向西班牙拉古纳的拉斯赖塞斯营地。(REUTERS/Borja Suarez)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;一群移民走向拉斯难民营西班牙拉拉古纳的 Raices 营地，2023 年 11 月 4 日。（路透社/Borja Suarez）&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;国际特赦组织官员表示该政策不公平。该组织表示，只有在对移民声称的年龄存在重大疑问且没有其他证据的情况下，才应使用此类测试。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;加那利群岛有八个。耶罗岛是受移民影响最严重的地区之一。该岛有人口 9,000 人。今年已有超过 11,000 名移民抵达该地。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;本月一个周末，500 人乘坐四艘船抵达耶罗岛。在这 500 人中，有 4 人死亡，另外约 15 人被送往岛上拥有 31 个床位的医院。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;克拉维霍表示，欧盟应该采取更多措施来解决非洲移民的问题。他说，当前的政策是在大多数欧洲人看不到的情况下“在边境虐待他们”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你知道母亲或父亲必须经历什么才能放养他们六岁或七岁的孩子吗？ 7岁的儿子和200名或更多不认识的人一起坐在一艘（小木船上），然后在晚上把他们扔进大海？”他问。 “这些人这样做并不是为了好玩。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Mas Fall 是来自塞内加尔的 17 岁女孩。他说加那利群岛应该期待更多像他这样的年轻移民。他说前往埃尔耶罗的 1,450 公里的危险旅程不会阻止人们。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“更多像我一样的人会来，”他用新学的西班牙语说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;我我是丹·诺瓦克。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;丹·诺瓦克根据路透社的报道改编了这个故事，供美国之音英语学习网使用。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;_______________________________________&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;机会&lt;/强>;&lt;em>;— n. &lt;/em>;an amount of time or a situation in which something can be done&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;overwhelm &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;— v. &lt;/em>;to affect very strongly&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;avalanche &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;— n. &lt;/em>;a sudden great amount of something&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 17 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Can a Two-State Solution Survive the Israel-Hamas Conflict?]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/can-a-two-state-solution-survive-the-israel-hamas-conflict-/7357867.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Thu, 16 Nov 2023 21:55:50 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-0a00-0242-3f46-08dbe6be5c4c_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;Smoke billows following an Israeli strike on Khan Yunis in the southern Gaza strip on Nov. 16, 2023. (Photo by SAID KHATIB / AFP)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;For 30 years, many nations around the world considered two states — one Israeli, one Palestinian — as the way to reach peace in the Middle East.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;VOA recently spoke to several experts about ideas for peace.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Many people believe two states remain the only path forward even after Hamas&#39; October 7 deadly attack and Israel&#39;s strong counter-offensive.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Israel says Gaza&#39;s Hamas rulers killed about 1,200 people and kidnapped more than 240 in their attack. Gaza&#39;s Health Ministry, which is led by Hamas, says more than 10,000 people have died in Israel&#39;s counter-offensive.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, political expert Uriel Abulof of Tel Aviv University believes the loss of life on both sides has not made peace impossible.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Abulof said the war has created a chance for people to “understand that this is not a conflict between the majority of Israelis and Palestinians, [both of whom] want to live in &lt;strong>;coexistence&lt;/strong>;, without radical leaders,&quot; he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&quot;On one side you have Hamas, which you have to deal with militarily, and on the other side are (Israeli Prime Minister) Benjamin Netanyahu and his coalition, which need to be dealt with politically,&quot; he told VOA.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Hussein Ibish is with the Arab Gulf States Institute that is based in Washington, DC He also believes that a permanent solution to the long conflict is possible only with a two-state model. He said it could be done in steps.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&quot;Israel must finally and formally accept the Palestinian right to a state and the need for it. The &lt;strong>;construction&lt;/strong>; and establishment of settlements must stop completely,&quot; he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ibish believes Israeli settlements in the West Bank, one of the two Palestinian territories, should be halted. Israel completely withdrew from the Gaza Strip in 2005.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ibish also said Palestinians must condemn the Hamas attacks of October 7 and promise to end the violence. He said the Palestinian Authority, which governs the West Bank, must be strengthened.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Actionable plan or unrealistic?&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Other experts are doubtful. Omer Bartov is a professor of Holocaust and genocide studies at Brown University in the American state of Rhode Island.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Bartov believes the two-state plan is unrealistic. He said it would create an economically weak Palestine that is dependent on Israel. He added that &quot;because there are between half-a-million and 750,000 Jewish settlers in the West Bank…their removal from the territory would mean civil war.&quot;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He also notes there are 2 million Palestinians who live in Israel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Israel captured the West Bank, along with East Jerusalem, from Jordan in the Six-Day War of 1967. It took Gaza from Egypt in the same war but withdrew from the territory.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Bartov said another possibility is a &lt;strong>;confederation&lt;/strong>; of Palestinian-Israeli states within the 1967 borders.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A confederated state, he said, would permit Palestinian refugees to return to territories their ancestors left when Israel was created. &quot;Jerusalem could be the common capital,&quot; he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&quot;There would be a difference between citizenship and &lt;strong>;residence&lt;/strong>;,&quot; said Bartov. &quot;Jewish settlers could continue to live in the Palestinian state but behave according to its &lt;strong>;regulations&lt;/strong>;. And the Palestinians could return from exile…”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, he said the single-state solution seems impossible because of the current war.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;A part for the US&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ibish of the Arab Gulf States Institute said US involvement would be important to any permanent solution.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said the US is the only country with the influence to guarantee a two-state peace agreement. However, he said, there is a large political cost in the US to put too much pressure on Israel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Bartov of Brown University agreed that no plan is possible without the US support on which Israel depends politically and militarily.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Without it, he suggested, the endless warfare would only continue.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Israelis and Palestinians “really don&#39;t feel there is hope. That&#39;s why the &lt;strong>;perspective&lt;/strong>; must be changed — how to make these two groups of people live side by side, not apart.&quot;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Gena Bennett.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Marko Protic reported this story for Voice of America. Dan Novak adapted this story for VOA Learning English.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;_______________________________________________&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;coexistence &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;— v. &lt;/em>;to live together in peace&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;construction &lt;/strong>;–n. the act of building structures with workers and heavy equipment&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;confederation &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;— n. &lt;/em>;a group of people, countries, territories or organizations that are connected by rules or laws but that govern themselves&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;residence &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;— n.&lt;/em>;&lt;strong>; &lt;/strong>;to live in a place and legally have it as your home&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;regulation &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;— n. &lt;/em>;rules and laws&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;perspective &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;—&lt;/em>;&lt;em>; n. &lt;/em>;the way a person understands or thinks about something&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 17 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Chinese-Taiwanese Relations at the APEC Meeting]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/chinese-taiwanese-relations-at-the-apec-meeting/7358027.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Thu, 16 Nov 2023 21:57:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/db5bdb85-8485-418d-a698-c28bd754466e_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;FILE - A US and a Taiwanese flag flutter outside a hotel as Taiwan&#39;s president was staying in Los Angeles, California, April 4, 2023. (AP Photo/Damian Dovarganes, File)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;Taiwan is taking part in the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) meeting in San Francisco, California this week.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Because it is an economic gathering, the self-governing island democracy of 23 million people does not face diplomatic restrictions from mainland China.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Taiwan&#39;s chief representative is a civilian, rather than a government official. It is an unwritten rule by China that members of the organization join as economic representatives rather than state officials.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;For the seventh time, Morris Chang is representing Taiwan. He is the 92-year-old founder of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company. Chang helped establish Taiwan&#39;s place as a top country for high-technology manufacturing in the electronics industry.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Taiwan has &lt;strong>;participated&lt;/strong>; in APEC since 1991 under the name Chinese Taipei. It began taking part just two years after the group began and the same year that China and Hong Kong joined.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Taiwan has depended on retired ministers and industry leaders, who are connected with the government but who do not have an office within it. The aim is to avoid angering China.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Politics at play&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China&#39;s economy has not recovered from the COVID-19 pandemic. The country has high youth unemployment and large amounts of debt in a weakened housing &lt;strong>;sector&lt;/strong>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, Chinese leader Xi Jinping is pushing ahead with his plan for China to retake its historical place as the center of cultural, political, and economic life in the Asia-Pacific area.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Taiwan has a multiparty political system that centers around local issues. There is wide agreement on political separation from China. That presents a special &lt;strong>;challenge&lt;/strong>; to the communist leaders of mainland China in Beijing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China wants to end US arms sales to Taiwan, including military planes like the F-16 fighter jet. China also wants the US to confirm it will not help the ruling pro-independence Democratic Progressive Party to keep power in Taiwan.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;John Kirby is a US National Security Council spokesperson. He said Wednesday that President Joe Biden will make clear to President Xi that the US, while following the law, will continue to provide &quot;self-defense &lt;strong>;capabilities&lt;/strong>; for Taiwan.&quot;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Chinese influence&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China has sought to influence Taiwanese politics through military threats. It also seeks influence through economic &lt;strong>;opportunities &lt;/strong>;on the mainland and local politicians.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Taiwanese media has also been persuaded to run stories critical of the current state of independence. That is done mainly through media ownership structures, which involve investments from the mainland.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;January&#39;s elections for the presidency and legislature will help decide whether the people want to continue independence or seek closer relations with mainland China.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Gregory Stachel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;The Associated Press reported this story. Gregory Stachel adapted it for VOA Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;_______________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;participate &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;. to be involved with others in doing something: to take part in an activity or event with others&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;sector &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. an area of an economy&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;challenge &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. a difficult task or problem&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;capability &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. the ability to do something&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;opportunity &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. a time when a particular situation makes it possible to do or achieve something&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 17 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[“Happy Thanksgiving“]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/happy-thanksgiving-/7355854.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Thu, 16 Nov 2023 22:05:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-c0a8-0242-9d6b-08dbe5e7f99e_r1_s.png&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>; &lt;p>;Americans will soon celebrate Thanksgiving. The holiday involves family, friends and food.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;A common expression Americans say to each other at this time of year is “Happy Thanksgiving.”&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;In the spirit of Thanksgiving, we will pay careful attention to the first word in the expression: happy. You will learn about the history and usage of this common, five-letter adjective – and its related noun form.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;Let&#39;s start.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;A helpful way to learn words &lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;We can bring words to life by learning about their histories. In this way, words become like close friends – we know their backgrounds, their beginnings, and how they have changed over time.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;Happy is – and always has been – a positive word.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;The Online Etymology Dictionary says the word dates to the 1300s. At the time, it meant “lucky, favored by &lt;strong>;fortune&lt;/strong>;... &lt;strong>;prosperous&lt;/strong>;” as well as “very &lt;strong>;glad&lt;/strong>;.” Soon after, it came to mean “greatly pleased and content.” The Dictionary also tells us that the majority of the words for “happy” in European languages first meant “lucky.”&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;From the word happy, we also have a noun form: happiness.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;When we compare the adjective “happy” with the noun “happiness,” we find that English speakers use “happy” much more often.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;That information comes from Google&#39;s Ngram Viewer, an online database that examines thousands of books.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Modern usages &lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;We have learned a little about the history of the adjective “happy.” So, how do English speakers use it in modern times?&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;Perhaps the most common usage is after linking verbs. These are verbs that link their subjects with their &lt;strong>;predicates&lt;/strong>;. Adjectives are commonly used after linking verbs to describe the subject.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;Google&#39;s Ngram Viewer says some of the most common structures involve the verb BE. For example, you are very likely to hear or read: “I am happy,” or “he was happy.”&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;We also use “happy” with other kinds of linking verbs – feel, seem, and others.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;Happy is also used with intensifiers – words that make an adjective stronger. Two of the most common, Google&#39;s Ngram Viewer tells us, are “so” and “very.”&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;These intensifiers are then used along with linking verbs. Consider these examples:&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;You look so happy! &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;We are very happy. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;They seem so happy. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;In all of these examples, the structure is linking verb + intensifier + happy.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;A few final words on the modern usage of “happy.” You are also likely to hear the adjective “happy” used to express kind wishes around some holidays – Thanksgiving, for one.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;In America, you will often hear statements such as this:&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;Happy Thanksgiving! &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;These statements are a kind of sentence fragment, or an incomplete sentence. There is no subject. The subject and main verb are understood between the speakers.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;A complete sentence would be “I wish you a Happy Thanksgiving” or “I hope you have a Happy Thanksgiving.”&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;We shorten these sentences because the first part is understood. That is how we arrive at “Happy Thanksgiving.”&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Closing thoughts &lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;In today&#39;s report, we explored one word: happy. You learned about its history and common usages with linking verbs and intensifiers as well as holiday wishes.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;You may or may not celebrate Thanksgiving where you live. But we can end this lesson by wishing you a very happy day.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m John Russell.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;John Russell wrote this lesson for VOA Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;_______________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;fortune &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n. &lt;/em>;something that happens by chance; the good and bad things that happen to someone&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;prosperous &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– adj.&lt;/em>; having success usually by making a lot of money&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;glad&lt;/strong>; &lt;em>;– adj.&lt;/em>; feeling pleasure, joy, or delight&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;predicate &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n.&lt;/em>; the part of a sentence that expresses what is said about the subject&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 17 Nov 2023 06:07:04 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[US, China Promise to Work Together on Climate Goals]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/us-china-promise-to-work-together-on-climate-goals/7356208.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Wed, 15 Nov 2023 21:55:38 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-c0a8-0242-d731-08dbe617c594_cx0_cy5_cw0_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;US Special Presidential Envoy for Climate John Kerry shakes hands with his Chinese counterpart Xie Zhenhua before a meeting in Beijing, China July 17, 2023. (REUTERS/Valerie Volcovici)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;United States climate diplomat John Kerry and Chinese climate negotiator Xie Zhenhua recently agreed to restart a suspended climate working group.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The agreement came at meetings from November 4th to the 7th held in Sunnylands, California, a joint statement released Wednesday said. The statement comes ahead of the COP28 meeting, the United Nations gathering on climate change, in Dubai starting on November 30.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The officials said their countries would aim for new targets for &lt;strong>;renewable &lt;/strong>;energy and limits on methane gas and plastic pollution. They said some differences remain, like how to stop using nonrenewable energy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&quot;The Sunnylands statement is a timely effort of &lt;strong>;aligning&lt;/strong>; the United States and China ahead of COP28,&quot; said Li Shuo. He is incoming director of the China Climate Hub at the Asia Society in Washington, DC&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China and the US are the world&#39;s two biggest producers of pollution from gases that some scientists say are warming the atmosphere. Li described the relationship between the two countries as “a precondition for meaningful &lt;strong>;global &lt;/strong>;progress.” He said the Sunnylands agreement will help “&lt;strong>;stabilize&lt;/strong>; the politics” ahead of the yearly United Nations climate talks in Dubai.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The re-launch of the working group marks the normalization of the climate relationship between the two countries following a break in 2022. That was when former US House of Representatives speaker Nancy Pelosi visited Taiwan, a self-governing island that China claims.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The officials said the working group will deal with areas in which the two countries can work together. They include reducing methane, increasing &lt;strong>;efficiency&lt;/strong>; and the economic system in which materials are reused, called the “circular economy.” Additionally, the group will exchange information on policies and technologies to reduce pollution. It will also aim to reduce forest loss and plastic pollution.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&#39;Unrealistic&#39;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China continues to approve new power plants that burn coal to guarantee its energy security.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The United States and China said they support a declaration by the G20, a group of the world&#39;s largest economies, to &lt;strong>;triple&lt;/strong>; global renewable energy production ability by 2030. They also agreed to speed up the use of energy resources other than coal, oil and gas.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The joint statement said they expect “meaningful” reductions in pollution from the power industry before 2031. But China described the idea of ending nonrenewable energy as “unrealistic.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The statement listed additional points of agreement. Both sides said they agreed to include methane in their 2035 climate goals. It is the first time China has made such a promise. They also promised to start “at least five” large projects in which they will work together to capture, use and store carbon by the end of 2030.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Li said COP28, the yearly UN climate meeting, still &quot;has its work cut out,&quot; especially with nonrenewable energy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“China also needs to consider what further &lt;strong>;ambition&lt;/strong>; can be brought to COP,” he added. “Stopping the approval of new coal power projects is a good next step.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Gregory Stachel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;David Stanway reported this story for Reuters. Gregory Stachel adapted it for VOA Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;renewables &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;adj&lt;/em>;. restored or replaced by natural processes: able to be replaced by nature&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;align &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;. to join a group that is supporting or opposing something&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;global &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;adj&lt;/em>;. involving the entire world&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;stabilize &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;adj&lt;/em>;. in a good state or condition that is not easily changed or likely to change&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;efficiency &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. the ability to do something or produce something without wasting materials, time, or energy&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;triple &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;. to cause (something) to become three times as great or as many&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;ambition &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. the strong desire to reach a goal or aim&lt;/p>; &lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 16 Nov 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Older, More Diverse America by the Year 2100]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/older-more-diverse-america-by-the-year-2100/7354659.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Wed, 15 Nov 2023 21:56:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/ed45926a-5948-4202-940d-d786fd17db6d_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;FILE - A parking lot attendant signals for people going to the Immigration Center in Miaimi to park Friday June 13, 2008. (AP Photo/J. Pat Carter, File)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;The US Census Bureau is a federal agency that researches information about America&#39;s population, housing, and economy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The latest Census Bureau report shows that the US population will decrease with low immigration, and older adults will outnumber children by the end of the century. The report also says that white, non-Hispanic people will account for less than 50 percent of the population.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Census report offers an idea of what the nation may look like in the future. But it cannot predict unexpected events like a worldwide pandemic.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Paul Ong teaches public affairs at the University of California, Los Angeles. He said such predictions can help the US prepare for change, from health care for old people to the number of schools for the young.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Seeing that possibility also opens up &lt;strong>;opportunities&lt;/strong>; for action,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Population changes&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Population changes caused by birth and deaths are more predictable. They may also be caused by changes in immigration policy. Because of that, the Census Bureau offers three different predictions through the year 2100 based on high, &lt;strong>;medium&lt;/strong>;, and low immigration.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In all three situations, the US will become older and more &lt;strong>;diverse&lt;/strong>;. If there is low immigration, the population will decrease; medium or high immigration will increase the population.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;By 2029, the report estimates that older people will outnumber children, with 71 million people over 65 as compared to 69 million under the age of 18. The aging of the population is important because this will mean fewer workers. An aging population also means more deaths than births.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The report estimates that, by 2025, the share of the US population that is white and not Hispanic will be under 50 percent for the first time. Also, Asians will pass Hispanics as the largest group of immigrants by race or ethnicity.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Under the medium immigration estimate, the US population reaches its highest total at more than 369 million people in 2081. After that, the Census Bureau predicts a slight population decline, with deaths overtaking births and immigration.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;By the end of the 2090s, the report estimates that foreign population will make up almost 19.5 percent of people in the US The number is currently at 13.9 percent.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Immigration&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In the past, immigration was linked to economic opportunity in the US Today, immigration is caused by climate change, social issues related to dictators and violence, as well as ever-changing feelings about immigrants in the country.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;These issues make immigration more difficult to predict today, says Manuel Pastor, a professor of sociology at the University of Southern California.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Aliana Mediratta is a 20-year-old student at Washington University in St. Louis. She welcomes a future with a more diverse population. She believes immigration “is great for our society and our economy.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But that &lt;strong>;optimism&lt;/strong>; is affected by issues that seem to be getting worse, including climate change and gun violence.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I feel like I have to be optimistic about the future,” Mediratta said. She thinks that if she believes the worst will happen, it might stop her from doing the morally right thing, even if it is hard.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Gena Bennett.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Mike Schneider reported this story for the Associated Press. Gena Bennett adapted it for VOA Learning English.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;_______________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;opportunity&lt;/strong>;–&lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. situations that make something possible&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;diverse&lt;/strong>;—&lt;em>;adj&lt;/em>;. including different kinds of people&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;medium&lt;/strong>;—&lt;em>;adj&lt;/em>;. in the middle&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;optimism&lt;/strong>;–&lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. hopefulness and confidence about the future&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 16 Nov 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>